0.DispatchDescription: An old customer placed an order at Whitestone. To uphold Whitestone's reputation, the order must be completed!

1.DispatchDescription: The rest of the FAC wants the former security head of Serpent Eye to give them some security training.

2.DispatchDescription: A secret deal will take place at a drag ball, requiring the right person to sneak in and stop it.

3.DispatchDescription: The villain in the classified file has reappeared. We have pinpointed the event route.

4.DispatchDescription: The Syndicate thugs have been a bit restless recently. Maybe someone can infiltrate them to find out why.

5.DispatchDescription: The sponsor of the Big Belly eating competition has yet to issue the reward. After investigating, it appears to be related to an abnormal cash flow transaction.

6.DispatchDescription: Some anomalies have occurred along the Rust. Professionals are required to deal with them.

7.DispatchDescription: A new type of weapon has recently become popular in Syndicate. The overlord of Syndicate and the leader of the Legion decided to personally investigate.

8.DispatchDescription: A studio under Quinn Media wants to create an anime based on the Sinners. A certain braggart volunteered to help.

9.DispatchDescription: A series of suicide bombings have hit Syndicate. An explosives expert is required to investigate the incident.

10.DispatchDescription: The Bureau set up an intelligence base disguised as a carnival booth, providing magic shows, games and other services.

11.DispatchDescription: Recently, the contamination level of DisSea underwent wild fluctuations. The District of DisSea has requested our support.

12.DispatchDescription: Someone declared they want to assassinate a performer on the dance tour. To protect her, we're going to use a body double.

13.DispatchDescription: DisCity has many dark corners, especially in Paradeisos. Be extra vigilant and ensure that everyone working there has appropriate identities.

14.DispatchDescription: After an informant planted in a secret organization died in an incident, the organization also disappeared from DisCity. To uncover the truth behind this, the Bureau needs two key personnel.

15.DispatchDescription: A super-high-speed motorcycle developed by Turbine Tech has been stolen by the Biker Party. After switching hands many times, the task of locating the bike landed with Whitestone Industries.

16.DispatchDescription: Multiple fires have broken out across Syndicate, each quite distant from the others. The Bureau wants to know if there is a connection between the incidents.

17.DispatchDescription: At the invitation of the Eastside Public Security Bureau, specially-dispatched Sinners have been assigned to carry out routine security patrol, considering that it is a fixed route...

18.DispatchDescription: Regarding the recent scandal of this family, the Bureau suggests that relevant personnel be dispatched to deal with the matter. To ensure the success of the operation, another strong individual should provide support.

19.DispatchDescription: The parent organization's research institute has recently encountered several technical difficulties. Considering the extent of professional knowledge required, there seems to be only one suitable candidate.

20.DispatchDescription: There has been a recent murder case involving a group of scavengers by the Rust. Someone familiar with the environment there is required to investigate.

21.DispatchDescription: Some old books in the library had been lost. The Bureau suspects this is not a simple management error, but the key to another mystery.

22.DispatchDescription: The Bureau's book procurement work has officially started. The total book list is 19 pages long. It is not easy to find suitable candidates.

23.DispatchDescription: The Bureau needs to evaluate recent dispatch work and draft an outlook for future missions. One of your superiors is the right person to assist you.

24.DispatchDescription: A renowned art magazine invites a famous critic to write a special piece and pays handsomely.

25.DispatchDescription: A food factory has launched a number of new products, but sales have been poor. They need advice from a more professional food critic.

26.DispatchDescription: The paparazzi have made up some tabloid news about the Sinner idols. This must be stopped.

27.DispatchDescription: While remote control is possible, these industries still require the presence of decision makers in person when a major incident occurs.

28.DispatchDescription: In order to improve the efficiency of agriculture in Hess Village, as well as in a number of neighboring satellite towns, they need more professional equipment and talents.

29.DispatchDescription: When encountering prisoners who are difficult to interrogate, the Eastside Public Security Bureau always sends a request of assistance to the Bureau.

30.DispatchDescription: The sandworms of WhiteSands are in a frenzy. We need an experienced hunter to deal with them. It will be even better if we can figure out the reason behind the commotion.

31.DispatchDescription: The Corruptors of DisSea have become extremely active recently. The district has opened up unpopulated control zones for special commissioners to use.

32.DispatchDescription: Molecular cuisine has long been an urban legend among the epicureans of DisCity. This legend occasionally reappears.

33.DispatchDescription: The depot at Banyan Medical College has been ransacked, and a large number of medicines and blood samples have been stolen. It is necessary to trace the clues immediately.

34.DispatchDescription: A dusty old house in Paradeisos has recently been burglarized. The Bureau will send relevant personnel to sneak in secretly and investigate.

35.DispatchDescription: The guitarist of a well-known band in Eastside is going to miss a concert due to a broken arm. The organizers hope to find a qualified substitute.

36.DispatchDescription: Recently, the Eastside Zoo received a mysterious donation, but the funds ended up in a private account. The anonymous donor is furious about the situation and wants to investigate it personally.

37.DispatchDescription: In a place like the Shadow Arena, money and strong fists will make you invincible.

38.DispatchDescription: Some people borrowed an underground rock venue to sell prohibited items. An well-oiled industrial chain has been formed, and it is urgent for someone to investigate.

39.DispatchDescription: Someone in Syndicate is using the Undertaker's name to do evil things, igniting the Undertaker's wrath.

40.DispatchDescription: Swarms of Corruptors have appeared on the edge of DisSea. We need a team crazy enough to destroy them.

41.DispatchDescription: A new concept kitchenware manufacturer hopes to find a famous chef to endorse its products.

42.DispatchDescription: Some highly classified surveillance missions have very high technical requirements for disguise.

43.DispatchDescription: A copycat has appeared among an infamous band of robbers! For some, this is completely intolerable.

44.DispatchDescription: An edible desert plant is growing successfully in the Bureau's green belt. Try planting in the experimental field in WhiteSands.

45.DispatchDescription: The most elite ikebana conference in Eastside has invited a Sinner to attend - after all, she is the most popular ikebana master in Eastside.

46.DispatchDescription: The Bureau needs to monitor an upper class banquet. All the participants are either rich or aristocratic, so be extra careful.

47.DispatchDescription: All the items of a large auction house have been replaced with fakes. The case details need to be investigated by special personnel.

48.DispatchDescription: Residents in some areas of Eastside often suffer from nightmares. It is necessary to find out why.

49.DispatchDescription: Abnormal levels of radiation have been detected near an amusement park. Experts are required to deal with it.

50.DispatchDescription: This mission requires someone to integrate into Syndicate with the calmest attitude, and to always be alert for the slightest of disturbances. This kind of daily surveillance is best-suited for Syndicate locals.

51.DispatchDescription: Recently, there have been sightings of a new species along the Rust. To determine whether or not they are Corruptors or some other mutated monsters, qualified professionals need to go to investigate.

52.DispatchDescription: There has been a number of missing pet cases in Eastside. The search for missing pets and the search for fugitives shall be carried out simultaneously.

53.DispatchDescription: The FAC headquarters issued a notice to the Bureau requesting an educational exchange, to which many Sinners scoffed and sneered.

54.DispatchDescription: There are rumors circulating about a haunted film crew. Upon reviewing the footage, we are going to control the relevant information.

55.DispatchDescription: There is news that a psychiatric treatment center is imprisoning its patients. We will dispatch the most elite team to investigate.

56.DispatchDescription: Of all the disguised venues used by the Bureau, the maid cafe is without a doubt the strangest of them all.

57.DispatchDescription: DisCity is always overflowing with injuries, which ensures that the medical team will always get the highest dispatch subsidy.

58.DispatchDescription: The cooperation with Banyan Medical College and SALVA is advancing in an orderly manner. Relevant technical data must be strictly protected.

59.DispatchDescription: Syndicate rappers are preparing an epic rap battle, for which the Public Security Bureau has specially invited a professional judge.

60.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Court has recently been flooded by complaints. Some have even threatened to make the lawyers and judges pay the price in blood for unjust rulings. The Ministry of Internal Affairs is very interested in this information.

61.DispatchDescription: The recent surge in stowaways along the Rust has prompted the Eastside Public Security Bureau to find out who's behind the phenomenon.

62.DispatchDescription: There has been a huge inflow of funds into Yagyu's accounts. According to relevant intelligence, they are trying to launch a new "hunt" and must be stopped.

63.DispatchDescription: A new Whitestone company has appeared in Syndicate, and its business is booming. This has enraged the real Whitestone boss.

64.DispatchDescription: Dis-Mart wants to dabble in the sports equipment business. They have sent the Bureau an ad shoot proposal, along with a huge sum of money.

65.DispatchDescription: Dis-Mart is preparing to formally sign a cooperation agreement with the Bureau, but the Bureau has some different opinions on the sharing ratio in the contract.

66.DispatchDescription: Abnormal fluctuations have appeared in this cycle's Tide of Ashes. The Secret Society Matrix wants to discover the reason behind this phenomenon.

67.DispatchDescription: A family in Paradeisos wants to test their recently updated security system. They have contacted the Bureau through personal connections.

68.DispatchDescription: A large number of Corruptors have appeared in DisSea, and medical staff are buckling under the pressure. The District of DisSea has issued a rescue order to the whole city.

69.DispatchDescription: Thou Voodoos seem to be researching how to manipulate dead bodies. The Bureau must take preemptive actions for the physical & mental health of DisCity residents.

70.DispatchDescription: A Bureau informant stationed within a certain company has mysteriously disappeared. Perhaps you can send a spy to conduct an undercover investigation.

71.DispatchDescription: A series of fraud cases has taken Eastside by storm. Rumor has it that the cases are linked to orphans at an Eastside orphanage. A certain someone is very interested in these rumors.

72.DispatchDescription: Rumor has it that toy puppets have come to life and are roaming along the Rust. The Bureau needs to determine the veracity of these rumors.

73.DispatchDescription: For better mission results, the Bureau has instituted some basic literacy courses for certain Sinners.

74.DispatchDescription: In the Bureau's special training sessions, Sinners form one-on-one study groups and help each other in their areas of strength.

75.DispatchDescription: Nirvana Logistics hopes to improve the beacon network in WhiteSands and provide the most accurate navigation guidance to the ships there. To this end, they have carried out in-depth cooperation with the Bureau.

76.DispatchDescription: A sudden sandstorm has caused Nirvana Logistics to lose several sand ships. We wish to find them and bring them back safely.

77.DispatchDescription: An ornamental snake in an Eastside zoo has escaped and caused injuries, sparking public panic. To capture it as soon as possible, the Public Security Bureau is in urgent need of assistance from professionals versed in snake behaviors.

78.DispatchDescription: A novice Eastside blacksmith claims to be the apprentice of the city's top weaponsmith, luring in numerous clients with that title. This greatly vexes the top weaponsmith of Eastside who's never taken any apprentices.

79.DispatchDescription: A popular toy shop is launching a limited edition new product. People are already queuing outside the shop overnight to purchase it.

80.DispatchDescription: A new sculpture museum is being prepared in the Eastside. The person in charge contacted the Bureau, wanting to hire a professional as an art consultant.

81.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Library will be hosting a classical art and literature conference recently, and a certain enthusiast submitted an early application to participate.

82.DispatchDescription: A series of thefts of works on display by a master artist, followed by a large number of well-made forgeries on the local black market, are suspected to be the work of a professional group and need to be investigated thoroughly.

83.DispatchDescription: Corruptors from an unknown source have attacked a certain location. By request, the Bureau sends professionals to help.

84.DispatchDescription: A well-known orchestra is recruiting new musicians and organizing a mass audition. Someone is tempted to try out after learning about the news.

85.DispatchDescription: An Outlander busker group seems very suspicious. The Bureau decides to immediately send staff on an undercover investigation.

86.DispatchDescription: A film academy based in Eastside is organizing a lecture on filmmaking for its students. The administration contacts the MBCC to invite a certain master filmmaker to give the lecture.

87.DispatchDescription: The MBCC has recently acquired some teaching materials on photography and photobooks by distinguished artists. The news brings endless joy to a certain shutterbug, who wastes no time in sending in a request.

88.DispatchDescription: A Sinner who is passionate about photography has been yearning to travel to the north and capture its spectacular scenery. It just so happens that another Sinner is being sent on a mission to the north, so the shutterbug sends in a request, asking Chief for permission to tag along.

89.DispatchDescription: An MBCC staffer who is opening a shop in their hometown invites a certain Sinner to perform a lion dance at the grand opening.

90.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau reports that some outlaws have been disguising as board game players. The Bureau sends someone versed in this kind of activity to assist in the arrest.

91.DispatchDescription: According to credible sources, a suspect has been frequenting the dodgy entertainment facilities in Eastside. You need someone who's familiar with the environment to carry out research and collect evidence.

92.DispatchDescription: A slippery fraud gang has recently become a headache for the Public Security Bureau. The Bureau thus sends a resourceful and eloquent Sinner for support.

93.DispatchDescription: A well-known school in Eastside is holding an open academic event that welcomes people from all walks of life to participate. An aspiring teacher in the Bureau is requesting to go there for a tour.

94.DispatchDescription: A group of violent individuals are reportedly hiding among brawling civilians. However, due to the target location's complicated situation, it is necessary to send experienced personnel to investigate.

95.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau has received a tip-off about an illegal slaughterhouse with unsanitary conditions that reportedly caused many animals to become seriously infected. They are asking the Bureau to send someone familiar with animals to help.

96.DispatchDescription: The Bureau needs a keen listener for others to confide in, and designates a room designed to look like the starry cosmos as a place to vent.

97.DispatchDescription: A celebrity nose insured for 300 million has been broken. Conflict ensues as the insurance company cannot afford to pay. A seasoned cosmetic surgeon is needed to intervene.

98.DispatchDescription: The Bureau receives a request to help restore some physical evidence damaged at the crime scene.

99.DispatchDescription: There have been a number of recent crimes mimicking the Foggy Night Mystery, and a Sinner with knowledge of this urban legend is needed to go to the rescue.

100.DispatchDescription: A building collapse has left many people buried under the rubble, and a Sinner who can ignore physical obstacles is urgently needed to rescue them.

101.DispatchDescription: New adventure lore has taken the city by storm, and two enthusiasts are eager to explore it.

102.DispatchDescription: The owner of a highly anticipated restaurant in Eastside is inviting a famous gourmet to try the food on the day of the opening ceremony.

103.DispatchDescription: An up-and-coming artist in Eastside is organizing a solo exhibition on the theme of "The Ocean", and he has contacted the Bureau in the hope that he can get some material and inspiration from a certain Sinner.

104.DispatchDescription: The MBCC receives a request from the Public Security Bureau to send in two Sinners, who are capable of disguising their personalities, to assist in the investigation of the mysterious disappearance of Eastsiders.

105.DispatchDescription: The FAC has organized a joint exercise competition and requests an experienced former FAC officer to participate.

106.DispatchDescription: A fashion studio in Eastside is facing a burst of orders on the eve of a fashion show, and is short of manpower, urgently needing the assistance of a professional tailor.

107.DispatchDescription: A number of cases suspected to be modeled after the "Garden" have been reported in a certain area. The Public Security Bureau applies to the MBCC for dispatching Garden-related personnel to assist in the investigation.

108.DispatchDescription: An Eastside socialite sent an invitation for an eccentric underground music meetup. A Sinner with broad taste in music claimed the invitation and plans to record the music event with her Schorl.

109.DispatchDescription: A mysterious case occurred somewhere in Eastside. The Public Security Bureau is urgently requesting a professional with deductive skills from the Bureau to assist in solving the case.

110.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau suspects an illicit manufacturer of dangerous goods is operating under the guise of selling stage props. They need the Bureau to dispatch someone skilled in identifying contraband for investigation.

111.DispatchDescription: A suspected Mania incident occurred at an open-air bath in Eastside. Because the bath has a unique nighttime theme, a Sinner passionate about bathing has made strong requests to go and investigate.

112.DispatchDescription: A batch of crocodiles has gone missing from an Eastside zoo. The Public Security Bureau has caught the culprit, but the crocodiles are nowhere to be found. They urgently need a Sinner who is a wildlife expert to assist in the search.

113.DispatchDescription: Someone claims to be able to concoct the legendary Immortal Fragrance, and is using it as a selling point to hold an auction and make a profit. A Sinner who is a perfume connoisseur is volunteering to go, and will either admire a masterpiece or expose a fraud.

114.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Public Security Bureau needs to disguise police officers as noble ladies for an undercover investigation, and wants the help of a Sinner who is a fashion and perfume connoisseur.

115.DispatchDescription: Recently the number of insomnia patients received by Eastside Hospital has climbed sharply, most of which are allegedly induced by the fear of the scary urban legend, and are in urgent need of hypnosis ASMR programs to assist in their treatment.

116.DispatchDescription: A fun snack site has just started up and wants to make a name for itself quickly. Therefore it needs an streamer to live-stream the sampling of weird snacks.

117.DispatchDescription: A late-night variety show in Eastside has seen its ratings fall, and is desperate to hire a critic who can do the whole job to star in the show and comment on hot social and current events.

118.DispatchDescription: Recently, many citizens have reported feeling watched by their daughter's dolls, suspecting that a peeping gang has put their modified toys into the market. A Sinner who is proficient in toy design and manufacturing is urgently needed to assist with the investigation.

119.DispatchDescription: Eastside is hosting a low-budget niche sci-fi film festival. A certain Sinner who yearns to gain inventive inspiration from films is eager to participate.

120.DispatchDescription: A detective culture club in Eastside organized a fun detective prop design competition, urgently requiring a judge with profound knowledge of fun prop invention and detective prop design to participate in the reviewing process.

121.DispatchDescription: The Bureau plans to compile a comprehensive history document of the rise and development of Rustfire. They need those in the know to assist them.

122.DispatchDescription: A research institute has developed a new model of pistol and urgently needs a firearm expert for testing and evaluation.

123.DispatchDescription: The Bureau has been busy with official duties recently and doesn't have enough time for housekeeping. Two Sinners have decided to work together to complete a major cleanup.

124.DispatchDescription: An entertainment company has launched a new talent show, this time with the theme of finding future musical stars. They are urgently recruiting audience judges to participate in the filming. A certain Sinner volunteers to go and uncover the hidden talents.

125.DispatchDescription: An association in Eastside has organized a busking contest which audience can watch for free and cast their votes. Hearing about this, a certain Sinner is eager to participate in it, confident that the champion title shall go to no one else.

126.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau is vigorously developing sonic weapons and urgently hiring Sinners capable of using sonic attacks and skilled in invention and creation to participate in the project.

127.DispatchDescription: The MBCC received a request from the Public Security Bureau. Explosives have been planted into a giant clock in an Eastside landmark. The device's mechanism is complex and dangerous, so they require urgent assistance from a Sinner with extensive knowledge of mechanical structures.

128.DispatchDescription: A journal market event is being held in Eastside. A certain Sinner insists that immense unknown danger lurks within and volunteers to go and eliminate the threats.

129.DispatchDescription: A mass kidnapping incident has taken place at an all-girls high school in Eastside. At the request of the Public Security Bureau, the MBCC urgently sends two Sinners to infiltrate the school disguised as students and secretly execute a hostage rescue plan.

130.DispatchDescription: A collection of valuable original copies of Outland books has recently been stolen from the Eastside Library. Assistance from a relevant scholar is urgently required to retrieve and authenticate them.

131.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Culinary Festival is about to commence, and the organizer has extended a friendly invitation to the Bureau. Having seen the invitation, a certain Sinner volunteers to honor it.

132.DispatchDescription: Recently, several models of an Eastside luxury children's clothing brand have gone missing after photo shoots. Send two Sinners to go undercover in disguise and uncover the truth.

133.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau has recently received complaints about a suspicious self-claimed master holding seminars titled *Communication with the Sun* everywhere. Send a Sinner to investigate.

134.DispatchDescription: Eastside's Idle People Society has recently organized a space-out contest with a huge cash prize for the winner, attracting many strong contestants capable of spacing out for over ten hours. This seems to have unusually piqued the interest of a certain Sinner.

135.DispatchDescription: Feeling a lack of combat strength in complex environments like narrow alleys, the Eastside Public Security Bureau is urgently seeking a fighting coach seasoned in street brawls to boost their training quality.

136.DispatchDescription: A well-known gift shop chain is expanding into Syndicate and launching a limited edition toy for the region. Upon learning that, several Sinners eagerly volunteer for missions in that area.

137.DispatchDescription: A renowned apple juice manufacturer in Eastside has launched a new tasting event for juices of various concentrations. A certain Sinner immediately submits thirty reports to apply to join the event.

138.DispatchDescription: In light of the recent surge in online dating scams, the Eastside Public Security Bureau is urgently seeking a Sinner with a charming voice who knows how to appeal to young netizens for their anti-fraud audio recordings.

139.DispatchDescription: A new masked dating show by an Eastside entertainment company with the catchphrase *Win your heart with one sentence* has become an instant hit. Two Sinners particularly confident in sweet talk volunteer for the next audition.

140.DispatchDescription: While patrolling around DisSea, a patrol discovers a temporary shelter built by an elderly man. Due to his superstitious beliefs, the team has difficulty communicating with him. Assistance from someone familiar with local religious customs is urgently required to persuade him to move.

141.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau receives a tip-off that a criminal group is circulating illegal content in the form of vintage discs. Assistance from an enthusiast with extensive knowledge is required to help identify them.

142.DispatchDescription: A major robbery happened at an Eastside bank. The suspect's M.O. highly resembles that of a serial robber once notorious in the city. A copycat crime is suspected. Assistance from a suitable operative is required to solve the case.

143.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau is planning to reactivate its internal forum. The forum is currently in disarray and rampant with false information due to the long lack of management. A Sinner familiar with this type of management task is needed to aid its organization.

144.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau has intercepted some transactional data sent by a criminal gang, but it is scattered with dark web jargon and encrypted links that are hard to decode quickly. They urgently need someone with relevant knowledge to assist in cracking it.

145.DispatchDescription: A group of children often gathers to play in a dangerous area where the patrol works. They have repeatedly ignored warnings and have now become a disturbance. The Bureau needs to send two Sinners who can quickly earn the children's respect to help remove them.

146.DispatchDescription: Nirvana Tech's prestigious programming institute for young children is recruiting a computer programming expert to conduct an educational seminar during its Science Month.

147.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Union is compiling an employee relations manual. They are urgently seeking a Sinner well versed in the subject to assist in their research.

148.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Sport Bureau is holding a ball game tournament which will include matches for all popular ball games open to all citizens. The MBCC needs to send its own participants with relevant experience.

149.DispatchDescription: It's recently been discovered that people are exploiting bugs in video games to generate income by illegally transferring large amounts of resources, severely disrupting the equilibrium in these games. Assistance from a Sinner with relevant knowledge is required to aid the investigation.

150.DispatchDescription: According to credible leads, a crime boss long pursued by the Public Security Bureau has fled to WhiteSands. With the outlaw's whereabouts unknown, the Bureau decides to secretly issue a huge bounty to recruit a Sinner from WhiteSands for the capture operation.

151.DispatchDescription: A violent dispute due to sales competition has broken out between two neighboring businesses on an Eastside shopping street. An experienced mediator with business management knowledge is urgently required to prevent further property damage from the escalating situation.

152.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau's new creative merchandise has hit its lowest sales record and is making severe losses. An experienced management expert is required to provide business consultation.

153.DispatchDescription: A famous dessert parlor in Eastside faces backlash over their new seasonal item containing too much sugar. To salvage their reputation, the shop is organizing a tasting event. A certain Sinner with a passion for exotic Outland desserts has volunteered to participate.

154.DispatchDescription: According to credible leads, an online scammer long sought by the Public Security Bureau will make an appearance at an upcoming speech impersonation contest. A Sinner skilled in imitating speech patterns is required to enter the finals and gather evidence.

155.DispatchDescription: A criminal group member was injured and became unconscious during a recent arrest operation by the Public Security Bureau. With the contact's letter lost, an expert in document forgery is urgently required for the mission.

156.DispatchDescription: Recently, multiple major Eastside sites have been under frequent attack. Rumor has it that these are the doing of an eccentric hacker. Cybersec is urgently looking for a Sinner with similarly peculiar thought patterns to help predict the hacker's next move.

157.DispatchDescription: The Eastside Paper Plane Society has finally raised enough funds to host a Paper Plane Contest. Upon hearing this news, a certain Sinner is immediately determined to participate in it.

158.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau has received intelligence that a criminal organization is recruiting impoverished workers from Eastside and West District to smuggle contraband into DisCity. A Sinner with extensive connections among these communities is required to assist in gathering clues.

159.DispatchDescription: Some Bureau staff members need to accompany their superiors to a noble family's banquet in Eastside. To ensure everything goes smooth, they must undergo proper etiquette training beforehand.

160.DispatchDescription: An entertainment company is launching a new current event talk show and is looking for pointed, attention-grabbing write-ups.

161.DispatchDescription: Some audio files containing crucial evidence are damaged. At the request of the Public Security Bureau, MBCC is sending a Sinner with expertise in audio recording and electronic devices to help restore them.

162.DispatchDescription: The FAC has detected an abnormal rise in M-value at a high school in Eastside. Preliminary investigation reveals that its students have been holding spooky tale-telling s√©ances after school. A request has been submitted to the Bureau to dispatch a suitable Sinner to assist in uncovering the truth.

163.DispatchDescription: The season is changing and flu outbreaks have emerged across regions. Recognizing this as a heaven-sent opportunity to accumulate good karma, a certain Sinner has eagerly requested permission to go out and provide free medical services.

164.DispatchDescription: SALVA has extended an invitation to discuss traditional Eastian medicine with a certain Sinner. As this Sinner is not a local, company of another Sinner of similar age who is familiar with the route from the Bureau to Syndicate is required.

165.DispatchDescription: The Public Security Bureau has received an arson threat targeting an amusement park. The sender is suspected of possessing Mania weapons. A Sinner skilled in creating illusions is urgently required to go undercover as a fairy at the parade and assist the Public Security Bureau in controlling the situation while guiding visitors to safety.

169.DispatchDescription: Residents in some areas of Eastside often suffer from nightmares. It is necessary to find out why.
